
CoreMedia Monitoring API - v1.1

Short description of the ReST API

  Shows all hosts known to the monitoring
    curl http://localhost/api

  View the information about the host $name
    curl http://localhost/api/$name


  Adding a Host to monitoring
  First, starting the service discovery, tehen create checks for Icinga2 and at last, create the Grafana Dashboards
    curl -X POST http://localhost/api/$name

  Re-add a host for monitoring
  Deletes all service discovery Data, Icinga2 Checks, and Grafana Dashboards
    curl -X POST http://localhost/api/$name/force

  Create an annotation that the host was created
    curl -X POST http://localhost/api/a/node/create/$name

  Create an annotation that the host was deleted
    curl -X POST http://localhost/api/a/node/destroy/$name

  Create an annotation for starting a load test
    curl -X POST http://localhost/api/a/loadtest/start/$name

  Creates an annotation for terminating a load test
    curl -X POST http://localhost/api/a/loadtest/stop/$name

  Creates an annotation for a deployment
    curl -X POST http://localhost/api/a/deployment/$name/$text

  Creates a free annotation (NOT TESTED Can lead to problems)
  $tags can contain a series of tags, which must be separated by '+'
    curl -X POST http://localhost/api/a/$name/$descr/$text/$tags

  Adds an Grafana overview dashboard to a group of hosts.
  $names can contain a series of Hostnames, which must be separated by '+'
  The hosts must already have been added to the monitoring.
    curl -X POST http://localhost/api/g/$names

  Re-adds an Grafana overview dashboard to a group of hosts.
  $names can contain a series of Hostnames, which must be separated by '+'
  The hosts must already have been added to the monitoring.
    curl -X POST http://localhost/api/g/$names/force


  Remove a host from monitoring
  Grafana dashboards are preserved and can continue to be used
    curl -X DELETE http://localhost/api/$name

  Removing a host from monitoring, including removing the Grafana Dashboards
    curl -X DELETE http://localhost/api/$name/force
